[assembly: System.Reflection.AssemblyDescriptionAttribute(@"ValueGuardian - Simplify Property Validation in C#

Overview:
ConditionCheck is a lightweight C# library designed to simplify property validation in your applications. It provides easy-to-use methods to check for null or empty values in various scenarios, helping you ensure the integrity of your data.

Key Features:

Logical OR and AND checks for mixed types.
Validate strings, collections, and model objects effortlessly.
Identify empty or null properties in model objects.
Easy integration into existing projects.
Usage:

Use IsEmptyOrNullUseOr for logical OR checks.
Use IsEmptyOrNullUseAnd for logical AND checks.
Utilize CheckModelProperties to identify empty or null properties in model objects.

Example:
// Logical OR check
bool result = Checks.IsEmptyOrNullUseOr(""Hello"", null, ""World"");
Console.WriteLine($""Result: {result}"");

